<p>I have seen code like this in ClojureScript repeatedly :</p>  <pre><code>(apply async/put! port (vary-meta val assoc :key *val*) args) </code></pre>  <p>I don't understand the repeated use of <code>vary-meta</code> along with <code>async/put!</code>, why is it needed ?</p>  <p>Seen for instance in <a href="https://github.com/circleci/frontend/blob/master/src-cljs/frontend/async.cljs" rel="nofollow">CircleCI frontend</a> code and <a href="https://github.com/ninjudd/eventual/blob/master/src/ninjudd/eventual/client.cljs" rel="nofollow">ninjudd/eventual</a>.</p>